readiness.insight: Based on your physical assessment, you are somewhat prepared for climbing Freel Peak, but there are areas where you can improve. Freel Peak is classified as a difficult climb, requiring a high level of fitness and endurance. While you have an active lifestyle and a good step count, your climbing readiness might be lacking in terms of specific endurance training and acclimatization to high altitudes. To better prepare, consider incorporating more specialized hiking and strength training exercises into your routine, focusing on cardiovascular fitness and muscle endurance. Additionally, gradually acclimatize to higher altitudes to reduce the risk of altitude sickness. If you're aiming to tackle this climb, I recommend starting with more frequent and longer preparation hikes, and perhaps even simulating high-altitude conditions.
